  overviewTitle="The finishing touch on your permanent tooth."
  overviewText="Implant restoration is the process of attaching the visible, functional part of an implant — the crown, bridge, or implant-supported denture — to the titanium post that has integrated with your jawbone. The restoration is what you see, what you chew with, and what makes the implant feel like a natural tooth. Using our iTero digital scanner, we capture an exact 3D model of the implant site and surrounding teeth, which is sent to our ceramist lab to fabricate a restoration that fits precisely and matches your surrounding teeth in color and shape."
  overviewExtra="Many patients in Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck have implant posts placed by oral surgeons or periodontists and then come to Thrive Dental for the restoration — the crown or bridge that completes the tooth. We work with all major implant systems and coordinate directly with your surgeon throughout the process. Our Bayside practice uses digital impressions for all implant restorations, which are measurably more accurate than traditional putty molds — resulting in crowns that seat correctly the first time with minimal adjustment. If your implant has fully healed and you're ready to complete your new tooth, call us to schedule the restoration appointment."
